	"The [Waste Marauder] vulture mount drops from Rotfeaster in Uldum.",
	"Chickens are domesticated bird critters found in many areas of Azeroth. They tend to avoid crossing roads, regardless of motivations.",
	"Clucks is an untameable, Common level 3 chicken battle pet. It is one of the battle pets of Old MacDonald in Westfall, along with Foe Reaper 800 and Teensy.",
	"El Pollo Grande, the Black Chicken of Death, is a huge black chicken accidentally summoned by Niby the Almighty in Felwood. Niby promptly declared that Vengeance will be mine! Death to Stormwind! Death by chicken!",
	"Hillpaw's Chickens are chickens located in the Heartland in the Valley of the Four Winds. They can be revealed to be a Wild Prairie Chicken, Amorous Rooster, Lost Hen, Disguised Marmot, or[Old Hillpaw's Prize Chicken].",
	'"Plucky" Johnson is a human, who has been turned into a chicken, found at the Mirage Raceway in the Thousand Needles. He is Magus Tirth\'s polymorphed apprentice. Wanting to avoid Tirth, he turned himself into a chicken to hide from the master mage.',
	'The Cloaking Chicken was a mechanical chicken located at Skull Rock in Durotar. Here it was found cloaking Sully "The Pickle" McLeary and Amber Kearnen, who were overlooking the Dranosh\'ar Blockade.',
	"Homing Robot OOX-09/HL is a mechanical chicken quest giver located on a small islet in the lake just northeast of Agol'watha in the Hinterlands.",
	"Homing Robot OOX-17/TN is a mechanical chicken quest giver located in the mountains just east of the Gaping Chasm in Tanaris.",
	"Homing Robot OOX-22/FE is a mechanical chicken quest giver located at Feral Scar Vale in Feralas. It can be found on the ground before the second cave.",
	"Mechachicken is an oversized mechanical chicken originally part of the Town-In-A-Box package. It was designed to provide food in case of emergencies.",
	"Amorous Roosters are chickens that appear during the Chasing the Chicken quest in the Valley of the Four Winds. When searching for Old Hillpaw's prize chicken, one may catch a rooster. Should this happen, simply dunk it.",
